Descrizione√à an annual herb tall up to 50 cm. The stem is erect and streaks appear on. The leaves, more numerous in the terminal part of the stem, are bipennatosette; they form a kind of involucre of bracts close to the flower. The flowers are light blue, very clear, a little showy and isolated; they also have a perianth petaloide. The stamens are numerous. The fruit is a capsule setticida with 10 loculi, and presents at the apex of the prolongations of the styles bent backwards. The seeds are black and angular contours. The flowering period is from may to July.
